'''Scott Lawrence''' (born [[September 27]], [[1960s#1963|1963]]) is an [[Wikipedia:America|American]] actor best known for playing [[Wikipedia:Sturgis Turner|Sturgis Turner]] in the legal drama television series ''[[Wikipedia:JAG (TV series)|JAG]]''. He is known for his voice role as [[Anakin Skywalker|Darth Vader]] in many ''Star Wars'' games, including [[Star Wars: TIE Fighter (video game)|''Star Wars: TIE Fighter'']], [[Star Wars: Rebellion (video game)|''Star Wars: Rebellion'']], ''[[Star Wars: Galactic Battlegrounds]]'', ''[[Star Wars: Force Commander]]'', and [[Star Wars: Episode III Revenge of the Sith (video game)|''Star Wars'' Episode III ''Revenge of the Sith'']]. In several of these vocal appearances, Scott Lawrence's voice was used over that of actor [[C. Andrew Nelson]]. He is considered to be the official "audio double" for the character voiced by [[James Earl Jones]]. He also voiced the character [[Jarek Yeager]] in the animated series ''[[Star Wars Resistance]]''.

